article.headline: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 69, Wagner 44
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- Jean Cajou scored 16 points, leading four Mount St. Mary's players with double figures in a 69-44 win over Wagner on Thursday night. Will Holland scored 12 points off the bench, Jeremy Goode added 11 and Shawn Atupem had 10 for the Mountaineers (8-14, 5-6 Northeast Conference), who have won three straight games. Cajou hit 4-for-7 from 3-point range and Holland was 4-for-6 from beyond the arc for the Mountaineers, who hit a season-high 12 3-pointers on 23 attempts (52.2 percent). Mount St. Mary's scored the first six points of the game and did not trail in the contest. Wagner (4-20, 2-9) was able to even the score at 9-9 with 13:14 left in the first half, but the Mountaineers used a 14-4 run to take a 23-13 advantage with 8:04 left before halftime and never looked back. Chris Martin and Doug Elwell each scored 11 points for Wagner in the loss.
